message.content: Now, as Hoastin reduced the throost, the pitch changed as the nose of the aircraft dipped slightly. The needle of the speed recorder swung gently through 8.0, 7.0, 6.0 before coming to rest at 5.0, "We're a bit ahead of time," said Hoastin, "we'll run in on minimum engine power." Geoffrey smiled. Hoastin talked of running in when they were still more than four hundred miles from their destination.
